#Text=The Portland Trail Blazers ( 36 - 17 ) defeated the Los Angeles Lakers ( 13 - 40 ) 102 - 86 on Wednesday at the Moda Center in Portland .
#Text=The Trail Blazers got off to a quick start in this one , out - scoring the Lakers 32 - 24 in the first quarter alone .
#Text=They also shot better in this game , going 41 percent from the field , while the Lakers went just 37 percent .
#Text=The Trail Blazers managed to secure a 52 - 48 rebounding advantage as well , helping to further their lead .
#Text=With the quick start and superior shooting , the Trail Blazers were able to coast to an easy win .
#Text=The Trail Blazers ' big three of Damian Lillard , LaMarcus Aldridge and Wesley Matthews all had very impressive performances Wednesday .
#Text=Matthews led the team , going 7 - for - 14 from the field and 3 - for - 7 from the three - point line to score 20 points , while adding five rebounds as well .
#Text=After shooting just 22 percent ( 2 - 9 FG ) from the field in Sunday 's game against the Rockets , it was good to see him get dialed back in and have a strong performance .
#Text=Aldridge was also big in this game , recording a double - double with 18 points ( 6 - 20 FG , 0 - 1 3Pt , 6 - 6 FT ) and 12 rebounds in 28 minutes .
#Text=He 's now posted a double - double in seven of his last eight games , as he continues to be a force for the Blazers .
#Text=Playing a factor in the win as well , Lillard posted 15 points ( 5 - 8 FG , 0 - 3 3Pt , 5 - 5 FT ) and eight assists .
#Text=He 's now averaging 22 points and 6 assists on the season .
#Text=Coming off the bench , both Meyers Leonard and C.J .
#Text=McCollum reached double figures with 11 and 10 points respectively .
#Text=The Lakers got the bulk of their production from their backcourt duo of Jordan Clarkson and Wayne Ellington .
#Text=In 27 minutes , Clarkson finished with 17 points ( 6 - 14 FG , 1 - 3 3Pt , 4 - 4 FT ) , six rebounds and four assists , as he was one of the few bright spots in the loss .
#Text=While he has n't been extremely consistent as a starter , he still has scored 14 points or more in three of his last four games .
#Text=Ellington , on the other hand , went 6 - for - 14 from the field and 2 - for - 3 from the three - point line to score 16 points , while adding eight rebounds and a steal .
#Text=It was his second strong showing in a row , a stretch where he 's combined for 34 points and 12 rebounds .
#Text=Coming off the bench , Wesley Johnson had the biggest contribution .
#Text=In 23 minutes , he finished with 12 points ( 5 - 11 FG , 2 - 4 3Pt ) and two rebounds .
#Text=It was his third straight game in double figures , despite averaging 9 points per game on the season .

#Text=The Trail Blazers ' next game will be on the road against the Utah Jazz on Friday after the All-Star break , while the Lakers will be at home against the Brooklyn Nets on Friday after the All-Star break as well .
